Egypt Studies Increase in Income, Corporate Taxes, Shorouk Newspaper Says

-- B y   O l a   G a l a l
-- 
2011-05-24T05:19:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-24/egypt-studies-increase-in-income-corporate-taxes-shorouk-newspaper-says.html
The Egyptian government is studying
an increase in income and corporate taxes on high-income
brackets starting in July,  Al Shorouk  reported, citing Social
Solidarity Minister Gouda Abdel Khaleq.  The Cabinet, which is still discussing whether to raise
individual income taxes, will likely support higher taxes on
company profits, the Cairo-based newspaper said, citing an
unidentified Finance Ministry official.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Ola Galal at 
 ogalal@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Stephen Voss  on   sev@bloomberg.net . 